1. **Unlimited Permission to Run the Program:**
You have the unlimited right to run the unmodified program. This means you can use the software for any purpose without any restrictions.

2. **Distribution Permissions:**
You are allowed to make, run, and distribute the covered works (software) that you do not convey to others, without any additional conditions, as long as your license to the software remains in force.

3. **Conveying Covered Works to Others:**
When you convey the covered works (software) to others, you must ensure that they receive the same permissions and freedoms you received. This includes providing them with the source code or a means to obtain it and making them aware of their rights under the GPL.

4. **Fair Use and Other Rights:**
The GPL acknowledges your rights of fair use and other rights provided by copyright law. This means you can exercise your legal rights while using and sharing GPL-licensed software.

5. **Sublicensing:**
Sublicensing (granting additional permissions) is not allowed under the GPL.